results.name: Triangle read by rows: T(n,k) is the number of graphs on n unlabeled nodes with upper irredundance number k.
comment: First differs from A332403 in row 7.
The upper irredundance number of a graph is the maximum size of an irredundant set. For any graph the upper irredundance number is greater than or equal to the upper domination number (A332403).
link: Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, Irredundant Set
